      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <ol class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">Sites are required to have a “site specific” waste management procedure.  This program is based upon:<ol class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">This waste management fundamental.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Appendix <xref href="EHS-02-006_appendices.dita#c1D1BCAA-BB01-11F0-1364-09173F13E4C5/li_umx_515_4zb"
                           class="- topic/xref ">A</xref> – any
                  regional-specific waste management guidance and/or tools that are more stringent
                  than the global waste management fundamental.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Appendix <xref href="EHS-02-006_appendices.dita#c1D1BCAA-BB01-11F0-1364-09173F13E4C5/li_qfr_gb5_4zb"
                           class="- topic/xref ">B</xref> –
                  site-specific waste management procedure , which includes any applicable local EHS
                  legal and regulatory requirements that are more stringent than the global and
                  regional waste management requirements. This procedure also includes any
                  additional requirements that are above and beyond the global or regional
                  requirements that the facility determines to be appropriate.</li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">The site-specific waste management program must be:<ol class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Documented and approved by the facility manager.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Placed into Appendix <xref href="EHS-02-006_appendices.dita#c1D1BCAA-BB01-11F0-1364-09173F13E4C5/li_qfr_gb5_4zb"
                           class="- topic/xref ">B</xref>
                  of this procedure.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Implemented and used with Space employees, contractors, and visitors.</li>
               </ol>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </section>
